05_Context
domain_key|section_key|domain_title|domain_definition|domain_scope|interpretation_guidance|intro_note|status|lookup_key
flow-state|05_Context|Flow State|Flow State describes the conditions under which attention becomes absorbed, effort feels steady, and progress starts to feel self-sustaining.|This domain looks at the conditions that make useful work easier to enter and easier to keep going across focus, ideas, movement, and conversation.|Read the ranked signals as likely flow conditions, not as a fixed identity. Lower-ranked signals are range to use deliberately, not weaknesses.|This is a ranked reading of the conditions most likely to help flow start, deepen, reset, and become useful.|active|flow-state::intro
06_Orientation
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|orientation_title|orientation_summary|score_shape_summary|rank_1_phrase|rank_2_phrase|rank_3_phrase|rank_4_phrase|status|lookup_key
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|paired|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Deep focus first|Start by looking at Deep focus. Bring in ideas, expression, and new angles when the work needs more range.|Your first two signals are close enough to read together. Flow is likely to come from how Deep focus and Creative movement work as a pair.|Your main route is focused time with one demanding problem.|What adds energy: ideas, expression, and new angles.|What helps you reset: movement, pace, and a change of physical state.|What to use deliberately: conversation and feedback before the work becomes too private.|draft|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::paired
07_Recognition
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|headline|recognition_statement|recognition_expansion|status|lookup_key
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|paired|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Considered ideas with room to move|You are most likely to find flow when focused thinking and idea movement can work together.|This pattern often shows up when you need enough quiet to understand the problem, but not so much structure that the work becomes fixed too early. You may move between careful attention and fresh angles until the work starts to feel both solid and alive. Physical Rhythm can help when attention gets heavy or static. Social Exchange becomes useful when the work needs to be tested outside your own process.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::paired
08_Signal_Roles
domain_key|signal_key|signal_label|rank_position|rank_role|title|description|productive_expression|risk_pattern|development_note|status|lookup_key
flow-state|deep_focus|Deep Focus|1|dominant|Deep Focus as one side of the pair|Deep Focus gives this pattern the patience to stay with a demanding problem. It helps the work become considered, grounded, and less reactive.|This can help you notice what matters, hold complexity, and avoid rushing to the easiest answer.|The risk is staying with the problem after the work now needs movement, feedback, or a decision.|Use focus to understand the work, then let the idea move before the thinking becomes too fixed.|active|flow-state::deep_focus::1
flow-state|creative_movement|Creative Movement|2|secondary|Creative Movement as the other side of the pair|Creative Movement keeps this pattern alive once focus has found the problem. It helps ideas shift, connect, and become more original.|This can turn careful thinking into work with freshness, range, and a clearer point of view.|The risk is opening another angle after the work already has enough material to finish.|Use new ideas to improve the work, not to keep it open longer than it needs to be.|active|flow-state::creative_movement::2
flow-state|physical_rhythm|Physical Rhythm|3|tertiary|Physical Rhythm as a practical reset|Physical Rhythm helps when the focus-and-ideas loop becomes heavy, static, or too mental. Movement, pace, or a change of setting can help attention return.|This can help you reset without abandoning the work or forcing concentration.|The risk is ignoring the need for a physical shift until the work starts to feel stuck.|Use movement when more thinking or more ideas are no longer improving the work.|active|flow-state::physical_rhythm::3
flow-state|social_exchange|Social Exchange|4|least_expressed|Social Exchange as useful outside testing|Social Exchange may not be your first way into flow, but it can help when the work needs to be checked beyond your own view.|This can help you find out whether the work is clear, useful, and understandable to someone else.|The risk is waiting until the work has been refined privately before letting anyone respond to it.|Invite one useful person to test the work while it is still easy to improve.|active|flow-state::social_exchange::4
09_Pattern_Mechanics
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|mechanics_title|core_mechanism|why_it_shows_up|what_it_protects|status|lookup_key
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|paired|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Why focus and ideas need each other|This pattern works by letting attention and possibility support each other. Deep Focus helps the person understand what matters, while Creative Movement keeps the work flexible enough to develop. Physical Rhythm resets the system when the loop becomes heavy. Social Exchange checks whether the result makes sense beyond the person's own process.|It may show up because neither pure focus nor constant idea movement is enough on its own. The work feels strongest when depth and originality can take turns without fighting each other.|It protects considered originality: work that has enough thought behind it, but still has life, range, and a clear point of view. The trade-off is that the person may keep refining and opening angles after the work needs a decision.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::paired
10_Pattern_Synthesis
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|synthesis_title|gift|trap|takeaway|synthesis_text|status|lookup_key
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|paired|deep_focus|creative_movement|physical_rhythm|social_exchange|Depth and originality working together|You can produce work that feels both considered and original.|You may move between focus and new ideas for too long before sharing, choosing, or finishing.|Let the pair work, then set a point where the work has to move forward.|This pattern is strongest when Deep Focus and Creative Movement stay in useful contact. Focus gives the work weight. Ideas keep it from becoming rigid. Physical Rhythm helps when attention becomes too still or crowded. Social Exchange adds the outside response that shows whether the work is clear to another person.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::paired
11_Strengths
domain_key|pattern_key|strength_key|priority|strength_title|strength_text|linked_signal_key|status|lookup_key
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|strength_1|1|Careful originality|You can stay with a problem long enough for better ideas to form. This helps the work feel thoughtful without becoming flat or over-controlled.|deep_focus|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::strength_1
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|strength_2|2|Fresh thinking with a base|Your ideas are likely to be stronger when they grow from real contact with the work. This gives originality more weight and usefulness.|creative_movement|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::strength_2
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|strength_3|3|Resetting the loop|When focus and ideas start circling, movement or a change of pace can help you see what matters next. This gives the pattern a practical way to clear the work.|physical_rhythm|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::strength_3
