domain_key|pattern_key|narrowing_key|priority|narrowing_title|narrowing_text|missing_range_signal_key|status|lookup_key
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|narrowing_1|1|Refining and reopening for too long|You may keep improving the work and adding new angles after it has enough substance to be tested or finished.|social_exchange|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::narrowing_1
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|narrowing_2|2|Thinking and ideating instead of deciding|Focus and ideas can keep feeding each other when the useful move is to choose what matters most.|creative_movement|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::narrowing_2
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|narrowing_3|3|Testing the work too late|You may wait until the work feels complete in your own process before checking whether it is clear to another person.|social_exchange|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::narrowing_3
13_Application
domain_key|pattern_key|application_area|guidance_type|priority|guidance_text|linked_signal_key|status|lookup_key
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|use_this_when|guidance|1|Use this pattern when the work needs both careful thought and a fresh angle. Give yourself enough quiet to understand the problem, then create room for the idea to shift before you decide what to finish.|deep_focus|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::use_this_when
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|watch_for|guidance|2|Watch for the moment when more focus or more ideas stops improving the work. That is often the point to move, pause, choose, or ask one useful person what is clear.|social_exchange|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::watch_for
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|develop_by|guidance|3|Develop by setting a visible decision point before you begin. Decide when the work must be shared, chosen, or moved forward so the pair does not keep circling.|social_exchange|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::develop_by
14_Closing_Integration
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|closing_summary|core_gift|core_trap|development_edge|memorable_line|status|lookup_key
flow-state|deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange|paired|This result points to a flow style built around a close pair: focus gives the work depth, and idea movement keeps it alive. You are likely to do your best work when both signals have room, then movement and outside testing help the result become clear and usable.|Your gift is the ability to produce work that is both considered and original.|The trap is moving between focus and fresh angles after the work now needs sharing, choosing, or finishing.|The useful edge is to set a point where the work has to leave the focus-and-ideas loop.|Let focus deepen the work. Let ideas move it. Then choose what carries forward.|active|flow-state::deep_focus_creative_movement_physical_rhythm_social_exchange::paired
